From a73bbd2d0a58f9ff45f6de6f6428e61a7b99a258 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: =?UTF-8?q?Daniel=20M=C3=BCller?= <deso@posteo.net>
Date: Mon, 6 Apr 2026 09:52:45 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] Add `let_with_type_annotation` lint

Add a new restriction lint that flags explicit type annotations on
`let` bindings (e.g., `let x: u32 = 42`). The lint encourages removing
the annotation and adjusting the right-hand side or surrounding code so
that the type can be inferred, reducing noise and making code easier to
refactor.

As a restriction lint it defaults to Allow, since type annotations are
sometimes necessary for disambiguation or when there is no initializer.
